Following the war against the [[Tuigan Horde]] in the {{YearlinkName|1360}}, sorrowsworn demons were to be found in the populations of those realms who'd lost their kin to the invaders, such as [[Cormyr]], [[Sembia]], [[Rashemen]], and [[Thay]].

They were also known to haunt fallen temples, eating the despair of [[cleric]]s forsaken by dead gods like [[Bhaal]] and [[Myrkul]], after their deaths in the [[Time of Troubles]] of [[1358 DR]].

A sorrowsworn demon lured by the lingering sorrow of [[Clan Melairkyn]] also entered [[Undermountain]]. It made its lair in [[Vankrakdoom]], in the tunnels adjoining the Chapel of Loss.<ref>{{Cite web enhancement/Vanrakdoom|23}}
